---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const siteUrl = "https://roofingaudit.co";

const jsonLd = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "AboutPage",
    name: "About Roofing Audit",
    description: "Meet Mudassir Ahmed — the person behind Roofing Audit. Learn why we audit roofing company websites and how we help businesses stop losing customers online.",
    url: `${siteUrl}/about/`,
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Person",
    name: "Mudassir Ahmed",
    url: `${siteUrl}/about/`,
    jobTitle: "Founder",
    worksFor: {
      "@type": "Organization",
      name: "Roofing Audit",
      url: siteUrl,
    },
    sameAs: [
      "https://www.linkedin.com/company/112202285",
    ],
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    itemListElement: [
      { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: siteUrl },
      { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "About", item: `${siteUrl}/about/` },
    ],
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="About — Roofing Audit"
  description="Meet Mudassir Ahmed — the person behind Roofing Audit. Learn why we audit roofing company websites and how we help businesses stop losing customers online."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-28 pb-16 sm:pt-32 sm:pb-20 border-b border-rule">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16">
      <p class="hero-reveal font-mono text-xs tracking-widest uppercase text-ink-muted mb-4">
        About
      </p>
      <h1 class="hero-reveal text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-[1.05]" style="--delay:80ms">
        I audit roofing websites<br />and find what's costing<br />you <span class="text-accent">real customers.</span>
      </h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder intro -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 border-b border-rule">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-20">
        <div class="lg:w-1/3" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-xs text-accent font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">Who I Am</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3 max-w-2xl">
          <div data-reveal style="--delay:80ms">
            <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-snug mb-6">
              Mudassir Ahmed
            </p>
            <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed">
              I'm a web developer and performance specialist who's spent years building, fixing, and optimizing websites for service businesses. My background is in full-stack development — but my focus has always been on the same question: is this website actually generating revenue for the business owner?
            </p>
          </div>
          <div data-reveal style="--delay:160ms">
            <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed mt-5">
              Roofing Audit started because I kept seeing the same thing — roofing companies paying $2,000–$5,000 for a website that was silently driving customers to their competitors. Not because the business was bad. Because the website was. No online booking, no pricing transparency, no trust signals, buried contact info. The same problems, over and over, across every city and every company size.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div data-reveal style="--delay:240ms">
            <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed mt-5">
              I started documenting what I found. After <strong class="text-ink font-medium">1,200+ audits across 11 states</strong>, the patterns became undeniable. The average roofing company website scores <strong class="text-ink font-medium">37 out of 100</strong> on our diagnostic. <strong class="text-ink font-medium">74%</strong> have no online booking. <strong class="text-ink font-medium">65%</strong> have no contact form. Most of these businesses have no idea. Nobody told them.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Roofing -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 border-b border-rule">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-20">
        <div class="lg:w-1/3" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-xs text-accent font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">Why Roofing</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3 max-w-2xl space-y-5">
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed" data-reveal style="--delay:80ms">
            Roofing is a trust-first, repeat-revenue business. When someone searches "house roofing near me," they're inviting a stranger into their home. Your website has to earn that trust in seconds. A single recurring weekly client is worth $7,000–$10,000 per year. The cost of a bad website isn't one lost booking — it's years of recurring revenue walking to your competitor.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed" data-reveal style="--delay:160ms">
            Yet the industry is underserved by web agencies. Most roofing companies get sold a template site by a marketing company that knows nothing about their specific conversion patterns — the importance of showing bonded/insured status, framing recurring plans, displaying pricing, or offering instant booking. The result is a site that looks "fine" but bleeds leads at every step.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed" data-reveal style="--delay:240ms">
            I chose to specialize because depth beats breadth. After 1,200+ audits in a single industry, I know exactly what works, what doesn't, and what the top-performing roofing websites do differently. That specificity makes every audit more valuable than a generalist review ever could.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The numbers -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 border-b border-rule">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-20">
        <div class="lg:w-1/3" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-xs text-accent font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">What I've Found</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-y-10">
            <div data-reveal>
              <span class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink block mb-2">37/100</span>
              <span class="text-[10px] text-ink-muted font-mono uppercase tracking-widest">Avg site score</span>
            </div>
            <div data-reveal style="--delay:80ms" class="border-l border-rule-light pl-6 sm:pl-8">
              <span class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink block mb-2">74%</span>
              <span class="text-[10px] text-ink-muted font-mono uppercase tracking-widest">No online booking</span>
            </div>
            <div data-reveal style="--delay:160ms" class="border-l border-rule-light pl-6 sm:pl-8 hidden lg:block">
              <span class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink block mb-2">65%</span>
              <span class="text-[10px] text-ink-muted font-mono uppercase tracking-widest">No contact form</span>
            </div>
            <div data-reveal style="--delay:160ms" class="lg:hidden border-t border-rule-light pt-8 col-span-2">
              <span class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-ink block mb-2">65%</span>
              <span class="text-[10px] text-ink-muted font-mono uppercase tracking-widest">No contact form</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="text-ink-muted text-xs font-mono mt-8" data-reveal style="--delay:240ms">Based on 1,200+ roofing website audits across 11 states.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24 border-b border-rule">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-20">
        <div class="lg:w-1/3" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-xs text-accent font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">How I Work</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3 max-w-2xl space-y-5">
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed" data-reveal style="--delay:80ms">
            Every audit follows the same 8-point diagnostic framework I've refined over 1,200+ reviews. No automated tools spitting out generic reports. I open your site, test every page on mobile and desktop, run speed diagnostics, review your Google Business profile, read your customer reviews, and analyze what your local competitors are doing better.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed" data-reveal style="--delay:160ms">
            The eight categories I evaluate: <strong class="text-ink font-medium">page speed</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">mobile experience</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">SEO health</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">SSL security</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">call-to-action clarity</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">review integration</strong>, <strong class="text-ink font-medium">contact accessibility</strong>, and <strong class="text-ink font-medium">competitor gap analysis</strong>. Each issue gets a severity rating and an estimated monthly dollar cost based on your traffic and average ticket size.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed" data-reveal style="--delay:240ms">
            You get a full diagnostic report — specific problems, priority rankings, and what each one is likely costing you per month. Not vague advice. Not a sales pitch disguised as an audit. Actual, actionable findings with numbers behind them.
          </p>
          <p class="text-ink-secondary text-base leading-relaxed" data-reveal style="--delay:320ms">
            <strong class="text-ink font-medium">10 audits per week.</strong> Each one done by hand. The audit is free — no credit card, no sales call, no catch. If you want help fixing what I find, we can talk. If not, you keep the report. It's yours either way.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-16">
      <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-10 lg:gap-20">
        <div class="lg:w-1/3" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-xs text-accent font-mono tracking-widest uppercase">Next Step</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:w-2/3" data-reveal style="--delay:80ms">
          <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight leading-snug mb-6">
            See what's wrong with your site.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/#audit"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-7 py-3.5 rounded-lg bg-accent text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-accent-hover transition-colors duration-300"
          >
            Get Your Free Audit
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M2 7h10M8 3l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
